column1:
`(?:.*
){8}\K(.*
)`  See [https://regex101.com/r/IjbZTP/1](url) with pcre option selected.  Then I could select all find matches or set cursors at all without the full match text being included in the find match - as it is if you use `(?:.*
){8}(.*
)` .  So I want to keep all that matched text out of the find match except line 9 for example.  But `\K` does not appear to be supported in vscode.
